# Find the command that add a new local user

# If you are signed in as root user, you can create new user at any time
# by typing:

adduser user_name

# If you are signed in as a non-root user who has been given sudo privileges,
# as demonstrated in the initial server setup guide, you can add new user
# by typing:

sudo adduser user_name

# 'adduser' command created a user, a group, and a home directory for user
